4) The buttons in dark mode are a little hard to make out. Maybe make
their border color contrast more. Similarly why a dull green for
link/highlight color? Blue is more generally recognized and used in the
calibre UI itself.

6) New category is confusingly named. From what I can tell its basically
a virtual library used to filter the shown books? Calling it Virtual
library will mean calibre users will be more likely to understand what
it is. Also perhaps add a line of text to it explaining what it does.

7) There appears to be no way to add custom columns (user created
columns) to the browse section. This should be added in system or ui
settings. You can see code for how to implement this in
bookshelf_view.py, see get_grouped_iterator() It would need to be ported
to RapydScript, of course.

9) I recently added "Offline mode status" to the home page. You need to
